<% provide(:title, "About the Challenge") %>

<div class="row">
  <div class="col-md-10 col-md-offset-1">
    <p>The Sodbury Challenge is an overnight orienteering exercise held in the
    Sodbury/Wickwar/Rangeworthy area of South Gloucestershire. The event is open to all Scouts, Explorers and Guides within the County aged between 10 and 18.</p>

    <p>The Challenge consists of a 5 and an 8 hour exercise with the winning team in each section being the team gaining the most points on the night. The 5 hour exercise is open to ages up to 14, the 8 hour exercise is open to those aged 14 and above. We also allow inexperienced teams and non-competitive teams who just want to take part, usually with a leader to help.</p>

    <p><strong>5 HOUR</strong> &ndash; A five hour exercise for teams of 3&ndash;5 members. First team out at 6pm and then the rest at 10 minute intervals.</p>

    <p><strong>8 HOUR</strong> &ndash; An eight hour exercise for teams of 3&ndash;5 members. First team out at 10pm and then the rest at 15 minute intervals.</p>

    <p>This year's event will take place on Saturday 13th October 2018.</p>
